Prof. Dr. Mohamed Shaker Almraqbi, chosen by Engineer Ibrahim Mahlab minister to take over the Ministry of Electricity and Renewable Energy, is Mohamed Hamed Shaker Almraqbi Professor of Electrical Power Engineering at the Faculty of Engineering, Cairo University.And who has held many important positions. He graduated from the Faculty of Engineering, Cairo University in 1968 and earned a doctorate in electrical engineering from the Imperial College, University of London in 1978 and worked teaching at the Faculty of Engineering, Cairo University, and began Consultative work since 1982, and established an office advisory in the field of electrical and mechanical consulting, and his office has a presence in a number of Arab countries, and worked as an engineer consultant for more than 1,500 project inside and outside Egypt, and worked with a number of global consulting offices.
